excerpt: "Introduction\nTransaction flow\nAPIs Table\nAuthentication:\nAPIs contract\n1. Card registration via tokenization\n2. Fetch Customer's saved vaults\n4. Transaction by token processing\n4. Tokenized Card's Life Cycle ( delete saved vault )\n\n\nIntroduction\nAs per latest development in Plural, Customer's Card can be tokenize on successful transaction. On the other side, Plural now capable to proceed with transactions through \"token processing\". Today Plural integrated with Edge as an aggregator to process transaction through tokenized card.\n\nCustomer can save cards into Plural system via card tokenization. Once customer gives consent on payment checkout page to save card then Plural  call card tokenization registration API to tokenize card but on successful 2 factor authentication only.\n\nTransaction flow\nprovisionNetworkToken -> GenerateCryptogram -> ProcessPayment Authentications -> Payments\n\nUsing card data , PineTokenIdentifier is getting generate form provisionNetworkToken(provisioning)\nUsing same pineTokenIdentifier,  we are generating the cryptogram.(provisioning) Which is a synchronous call inside transaction by token processing API of Plural.\nSame cryptogram and TokenizedCard details we are  sending to aggregator's Process Payments API to complete the transaction. \nPostman Collection\n\nhttps://www.getpostman.com/collections/ee31e4eb4e1dd4bd169c\n\nAPIs Table\n APIs exposed by Plural system to Merchant \n\nSr No\tAPI title\tURL\n1\tProcess Payment API\thttps://api-staging.pluralonline.com/api/v1/card/process/payment?token=i1I8ShaFc75Z02%2fUzQrDRfuSq14h%2fZBKyPhdlMKZ5zs%3d\n2\tFetch Customer's saved vaults\thttps://api-staging.pluralonline.com/api/v1/vault/cards?customerToken=STfVWQWJIp50kmVebbNM/w==&merchantId=120\n3\tTransaction by token processing \thttps://api-staging.pluralonline.com/api/v1/card/process/payment/tokenize?token=i1I8ShaFc75Z02%2fUzQrDRfuSq14h%2fZBKyPhdlMKZ5zs%3d\n4\tTokenized Card's Life Cycle (Delete of saved tokenized vault)\thttps://api-staging.pluralonline.com/api/v1/vault/card/{pineTokenIdentifier}/close\nAuthentication:\n                             All APIs must be authenticated with basic authentication mechanism. \n\nAuth's credentials \n\nValues \n\nusername\t\nMerchant Id\n\npassword\tMerchant access code"
